1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,810
2.

2
00:00:02,000 --> 00:00:05,090
But you've got to have brains to succeed.

3
00:00:05,680 --> 00:00:10,290
Intelligence excusitis, or I lack brains, is common.

4
00:00:10,560 --> 00:00:18,129
In fact, it's so common that perhaps as many as 95% of the people around us have it in varying degrees.

5
00:00:18,560 --> 00:00:26,450
Unlike most other types of excusitis, people suffering from this particular type of the malady suffer in silence.

6
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:32,210
Not many people will admit openly that they think they lack adequate intelligence.

7
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:35,410
Rather, they feel it deep down inside.

8
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:40,530
Most of us make two basic errors with respect to intelligence.

9
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:44,530
One, we underestimate our own brain power.

10
00:00:44,960 --> 00:00:48,850
Two, we overestimate the other fellow's brain power.

11
00:00:49,280 --> 00:00:52,850
Because of these errors, many people sell themselves short.

12
00:00:53,040 --> 00:00:57,650
They fail to tackle challenging situations because it takes a brain.

13
00:00:57,760 --> 00:01:03,090
But along comes the fellow who isn't concerned about intelligence, and he gets the job.

14
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:09,810
What really matters is not how much intelligence you have, but how you use what you do have.

15
00:01:10,240 --> 00:01:16,290
The thinking that guides your intelligence is much more important than the quantity of your brain power.

16
00:01:16,480 --> 00:01:19,729
Let me repeat, for this is vitally important.

17
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:27,009
The thinking that guides your intelligence is much more important than how much intelligence you may have.

18
00:01:27,440 --> 00:01:31,170
In answering the question, Should your child be a scientist?

19
00:01:31,170 --> 00:01:40,450
, Dr. Edward Teller, one of the nation's foremost physicists, said, A child does not need a lightning-fast mind to be a scientist.

20
00:01:40,560 --> 00:01:46,770
nor does he need a miraculous memory, nor is it necessary that he get very high grades in school.

21
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:52,850
The only point that counts is that the child have a high degree of interest in science.

22
00:01:53,440 --> 00:01:58,690
Interest, enthusiasm, is the critical factor even in science.

23
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:06,450
With a positive, optimistic, and cooperative attitude, a person with an IQ of 100 will earn more money,

24
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:15,170
win more respect, and achieve more success than a negative, pessimistic, uncooperative individual with an IQ of 120.

25
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:25,330
Just enough sense to stick with something—a chore, task, project—until it's completed pays off much better than idle intelligence,

26
00:02:25,520 --> 00:02:28,930
even if idle intelligence be of genius caliber.

27
00:02:29,280 --> 00:02:33,729
for stickability is 95% of ability.

